President Biden had a conversation with Prime Minister Netanyahu of Israel regarding the situation in Gaza and efforts to locate and secure the release of hostages, including American citizens held by Hamas. They also discussed facilitating the safe departure of foreign nationals from Gaza. President Biden expressed U.S. support for providing humanitarian aid to the civilian population in Gaza and emphasized Israel's right to defend its citizens in accordance with international humanitarian law. He stressed the importance of working towards a permanent peace between Israelis and Palestinians, highlighting that Hamas does not represent the Palestinian people. Both leaders agreed to maintain regular consultation through their national security teams.